g/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/customresource_discovery_controller.go:141, 144)\nDefines two verb sets for CRD resources:\n- Normal: [delete, deletecollection, get, list, patch, create, update, watch]\n- Terminating: [delete, deletecollection, get, list, watch]\n\n**7. kubectl auth can-i Verb Set** (staging/src/k8s.io/kubectl/pkg/cmd/auth/cani.go:108)\nDefines resourceVerbs for authorization checking: [get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete, deletecollection, use, bind, impersonate, *, approve, sign, escalate, attest]\n\n### Verb Validation Points\n\n**1. RBAC Policy Rule Validation** (pkg/apis/rbac/helpers.go:186-200)\nThe PolicyRuleBuilder.Rule() method enforces that when ResourceNames are specified, certain verbs (list, watch, create, deletecollection) cannot be used, as they operate on collections rather than specific resources.\n\n**2. Authorization Filter** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/filters/authorization.go)\nThe WithAuthorization handler extracts verb from RequestInfo and passes it to the authorizer for decision-making.\n\n**3. API Handler Registration** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/installer.go:registerResourceHandlers)\nRegisters HTTP handlers for each action verb, mapping storage capabilities to supported operations.\n\n**4. Resource Deletion Controllers** (pkg/controller/namespace/deletion/namespaced_resources_deleter.go, pkg/controller/garbagecollector/garbagecollector.go)\nValidate that resources support required verbs (delete, deletecollection) before attempting operations.\n\n**5. Resource Quota Controller** (pkg/controller/resourcequota/resource_quota_controller.go:559)\nFilters resources to only those supporting [create, list, watch, delete] verbs for quota enforcement.\n\n**6. CRD Handler** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/customresource_handler.go)\nManages HTTP handlers for CRD resources, respecting the verb sets defined in the discovery controller.\n\n### Key Enforcement Mechanisms\n\n1. **Authorization Attributes Interface** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authorization/authorizer/interfaces.go:34)\nThe Attributes.GetVerb() method documents supported verbs: get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete, deletecollection, proxy.\n\n2. **APIResource Verbs Field** (staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/types.go:1203-1205)\nAll API resources expose a Verbs list in discovery, enabling clients to determine supported operations.\n\n3. **Discovery Helper** (staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/discovery/helper.go:139-146)\nThe SupportsAllVerbs predicate enables filtering resources by verb support, used throughout controllers.\n\n4. **Metrics Verb Normalization** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/metrics/metrics.go:700-733)\nThe CanonicalVerb function normalizes verbs for metrics collection (e.g., distinguishing LIST from GET, normalizing WATCHLIST to WATCH).\n\n### Coverage Assessment\n\nThe audit confirms that Kubernetes v1.32.0 has comprehensive verb coverage across multiple layers:\n\n- **Verb Definition**: Centralized definitions in openapi, bootstrap policies, CLI tools, and request parsing\n- **Verb Mapping**: Clear HTTP-to-Kube verb translation in the installer\n- **Verb Validation**: RBAC rules enforce semantic constraints (e.g., no list/watch on named resources)\n- **Verb Enforcement**: Authorization filters apply verb constraints before handler execution\n- **Verb Discovery**: All API resources expose supported verbs through the discovery API\n- **Verb Usage**: Controllers validate verb support before calling APIs\n\nThe eight core verbs (get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete, deletecollection) are consistently defined across the codebase with proper enforcement at authorization, handler, and controller layers."
